# Testing Standards

## Three test types (all required)

### tests/unit/
Mocked LLM calls. One test file per agent.
Tests: schema validation, error propagation, field defaults.
Run on every commit.

### tests/integration/
Test the live API endpoints.
Must include test_api_contract.py which:
  - Calls real /analyze and /generate endpoints (mocked LLM)
  - Validates every field against api-contract.md
  - Checks numeric field ranges (scores 0-10, rates > 0)
  - Checks no schema field names in prose output fields

### tests/acceptance/
Real LLM calls. Behavioral assertions.
Tag: @pytest.mark.acceptance
Run separately — not in default pytest run.
Not mocked. Calls real API with real model.
Tests:
  - "bad proposal" → overall_score <= 4
  - "strong proposal" → overall_score >= 7
  - No snake_case field names in any prose output field
  - win_probability_score in range 0-10

## Gate
pytest (unit + integration) must pass before every commit.
acceptance tests run before every Railway deploy.

## conftest.py
Golden fixtures in tests/conftest.py:
  - sample_analyze_request: realistic job posting + weak proposal
  - sample_generate_request: realistic job posting only
  - sample_job_analysis: valid JobAnalysis for agent testing
  - sample_rate_analysis: valid RateAnalysis for agent testing
